Quote: ambrite n. yellowish-grey fossil resin found in NZ. [AMBER]
Notes: nf. 1982 Collins Concise Eng. Dict.

Date: 13/4/1888
Source: Otago Witness
Author:
Vol / Page: 36
Edition:
Quote: On examining SOME OF THE LIGNITES OF OTAGO, we find large trunks of trees, masses of leaves and twigs, matted together, and containing lumps of fossil resins known as ambrite, the whole forming a very excellent fuel for local purposes.
Notes:

Date: 9/8/1906
Source: Evening Post
Author:
Vol / Page: 8
Edition:
Quote: A piece of resinous substance lying on a shelf in the office of the Undersecretary for Mines attracted the attention of a Post representative to-day. The pressman was curious to know whence it came, and was informed that it was a lump of ambrite which had been found in one of the South Island coalmines.
